properties.name: objectExportOptions
properties.description: Export options for the object

properties.name: transparencySettings
properties.description: Transparency settings.

properties.name: strokeTransparencySettings
properties.description: Transparency settings for the stroke.

properties.name: fillTransparencySettings
properties.description: Transparency settings for the fill applied to the ObjectStyle.

properties.name: contentTransparencySettings
properties.description: Transparency settings for the content of the ObjectStyle.

properties.name: objectEffectsEnablingSettings
properties.description: The object effects enabling settings.

properties.name: strokeEffectsEnablingSettings
properties.description: The stroke effects enabling settings.

properties.name: fillEffectsEnablingSettings
properties.description: The fill effects enabling settings.

properties.name: contentEffectsEnablingSettings
properties.description: The content effects enabling settings.

properties.name: id
properties.description: The unique ID of the ObjectStyle.

properties.name: isValid
properties.description: Returns true if the object specifier resolves to valid objects.

properties.name: parent
properties.description: The parent of the ObjectStyle (a Document, Application or ObjectStyleGroup).

properties.name: index
properties.description: The index of the ObjectStyle within its containing object.

properties.name: preferences
properties.description: A collection of preferences objects.

properties.name: objectStyleExportTagMaps
properties.description: A collection of object style export tag maps.

properties.name: events
properties.description: A collection of events.

properties.name: eventListeners
properties.description: A collection of event listeners.

properties.name: transformAttributeOptions
properties.description: The layout attribute options to apply to any page item.

properties.name: enableTransformAttributes
properties.description: If true, enables the Dimension and Position attributes

properties.name: topLeftCornerOption
properties.description: The shape to be applied to the top left corner of rectangular shapes and all corners of non-rectangular shapes.Note: corner option differs from end join in which you can set a radius for a corner option, whereas the rounded or beveled effect of an end join depends on the stroke weight.

properties.name: topRightCornerOption
properties.description: The shape to apply to the top right corner of rectangular shapes

properties.name: bottomLeftCornerOption
properties.description: The shape to apply to the bottom left corner of rectangular shapes.

properties.name: bottomRightCornerOption
properties.description: The shape to apply to the bottom right corner of rectangular shapes.

properties.name: topLeftCornerRadius
properties.description: The radius in measurement units of the corner effect applied to the top left corner of rectangular shapes and all corners of non-rectangular shapes

properties.name: topRightCornerRadius
properties.description: The radius in measurement units of the corner effect applied to the top right corner of rectangular shapes

properties.name: bottomLeftCornerRadius
properties.description: The radius in measurement units of the corner effect applied to the bottom left corner of rectangular shapes

properties.name: bottomRightCornerRadius
properties.description: The radius in measurement units of the corner effect applied to the bottom right corner of rectangular shapes

properties.name: emitCss
properties.description: Emit CSS

properties.name: includeClass
properties.description: If true, class attribute will be generated for the style

properties.name: enableTextFrameAutoSizingOptions
properties.description: If true, the object style will apply auto-sizing text frame options.

properties.name: enableExportTagging
properties.description: If true, the object style will apply an epub tag and class.

properties.name: enableObjectExportAltTextOptions
properties.description: If true, the object style will apply alt text export options.

properties.name: enableObjectExportTaggedPdfOptions
properties.description: If true, the object style will apply tagged pdf export options.

properties.name: enableObjectExportEpubOptions
properties.description: If true, the object style will apply epub export options.

properties.name: basedOn
properties.description: The style that this style is based on. Can return: ObjectStyle or String.

properties.name: name
properties.description: The name of the ObjectStyle.

properties.name: appliedParagraphStyle
properties.description: The paragraph style applied to the text. Can also accept: String.

properties.name: applyNextParagraphStyle
properties.description: If true, applies paragraph styles using Next Paragraph Style settings, beginning with the Next Paragraph Style defined in the paragraph style associated with the object style (if any).

properties.name: enableFill
properties.description: If true, the object style will apply a fill.

properties.name: enableStroke
properties.description: If true, the object style will apply a stroke.

properties.name: enableParagraphStyle
properties.description: If true, the object style will apply a paragraph style.

properties.name: enableTextFrameGeneralOptions
properties.description: If true, the object style will apply general text frame options.

properties.name: enableTextFrameBaselineOptions
properties.description: If true, the object style will apply baseline text frame options.

properties.name: enableStoryOptions
properties.description: If true, the object style will apply story options.

properties.name: enableTextWrapAndOthers
properties.description: If true, the object style will apply text wrap, contour, and non-printing settings.

properties.name: enableAnchoredObjectOptions
properties.description: If true, the object style will apply an anchored object setting.

properties.name: fillColor
properties.description: The swatch (color, gradient, tint, or mixed ink) applied to the fill of the ObjectStyle. . Can also accept: String.

properties.name: fillTint
properties.description: The percent of tint to use in the ObjectStyle's fill color. (To specify a tint percent, use a number in the range of 0 to 100; to use the inherited or overridden value, use -1.)

properties.name: overprintFill
properties.description: If true, the ObjectStyle's fill color overprints any underlying objects. If false, the fill color knocks out the underlying colors.

properties.name: strokeWeight
properties.description: The weight (in points) to apply to the ObjectStyle's stroke.

properties.name: miterLimit
properties.description: The limit of the ratio of stroke width to miter length before a miter (pointed) join becomes a bevel (squared-off) join.

properties.name: endCap
properties.description: The end shape of an open path.

properties.name: endJoin
properties.description: The corner join applied to the ObjectStyle.

properties.name: strokeType
properties.description: The name of the stroke style to apply. Can also accept: String.

properties.name: leftLineEnd
properties.description: The arrowhead applied to the start of the path.

properties.name: rightLineEnd
properties.description: The arrowhead applied to the end of the path.

properties.name: strokeColor
properties.description: The swatch (color, gradient, tint, or mixed ink) applied to the stroke of the ObjectStyle. Can also accept: String.

properties.name: strokeTint
properties.description: The percent of tint to use in object's stroke color. (To specify a tint percent, use a number in the range of 0 to 100; to use the inherited or overridden value, use -1.)

properties.name: overprintStroke
properties.description: If true, the ObjectStyle's stroke color overprints any underlying objects. If false, the stroke color knocks out the  underlying colors.

properties.name: gapColor
properties.description: The swatch (color, gradient, tint, or mixed ink) applied to the gap of a dashed, dotted, or striped stroke. For information, see stroke type.

properties.name: gapTint
properties.description: The tint as a percentage of the gap color. (To specify a tint percent, use a number in the range of 0 to 100; to use the inherited or overridden value, use -1.)

properties.name: overprintGap
properties.description: If true, the gap color overprints any underlying colors. If false, the gap color knocks out the underlying colors.

properties.name: strokeAlignment
properties.description: The stroke alignment applied to the ObjectStyle.

properties.name: nonprinting
properties.description: If true, the ObjectStyle does not print.

properties.name: gradientFillAngle
properties.description: The angle of a linear gradient applied to the fill of the ObjectStyle. (Range: -180 to 180)

properties.name: gradientStrokeAngle
properties.description: The angle of a linear gradient applied to the stroke of the ObjectStyle. (Range: -180 to 180)

properties.name: textFramePreferences
properties.description: Text frame preference settings.

properties.name: baselineFrameGridOptions
properties.description: Baseline frame grid option settings.

properties.name: anchoredObjectSettings
properties.description: Anchored object settings.

properties.name: textWrapPreferences
properties.description: The text wrap preference properties that define the default formatting for wrapping text around objects.

properties.name: storyPreferences
properties.description: Story preference settings.

properties.name: frameFittingOptions
properties.description: The frame fitting option to apply to placed or pasted content. Can be applied to a frame, object style, or document or to the application.

properties.name: enableFrameFittingOptions
properties.description: If true, the object style will apply frame fitting options.

properties.name: enableStrokeAndCornerOptions
properties.description: If true, the object style will apply stroke options and corner options.

properties.name: arrowHeadAlignment
properties.description: The arrowhead alignment applied to the ObjectStyle.

properties.name: leftArrowHeadScale
properties.description: The scaling applied to the arrowhead at the start of the path. (Range: 1 to 1000)

properties.name: rightArrowHeadScale
properties.description: The scaling applied to the arrowhead at the end of the path. (Range: 1 to 1000)

properties.name: enableTextFrameFootnoteOptions
properties.description: Enable the text frame footnote options category of object style

properties.name: label
properties.description: A property that can be set to any string.

properties.name: properties
properties.description: A property that allows setting of several properties at the same time.

methods.name: setDimensionAttributeState

parameters.name: whichAttributes
parameters.description: Which dimension attributes do you want to enable or disable.

parameters.name: attributeState
parameters.description: Attribute state to be set, set true to enable and false to disable the attributes

methods.description: Sets the given dimension attribute state to enabled or disabled state

methods.name: setPositionAttributeState

parameters.name: whichAttributes
parameters.description: Which position attributes do you want to enable or disable.

parameters.name: attributeState
parameters.description: Attribute state to be set, set true to enable and false to disable the attributes

methods.description: Sets the given position attribute state to enabled or disabled state

methods.name: move

parameters.name: to
parameters.description: The new location relative to the reference object or within the container object.

parameters.name: reference
parameters.description: The reference object. Note: Required when the to parameter is before or after. Can accept: ObjectStyle, ObjectStyleGroup, Document or Application. (Optional)

methods.description: Moves the ObjectStyle to the specified location.

parameters.name: replacingWith
parameters.description: The style to apply in place of the deleted style. (Optional)

methods.name: insertLabel
methods.description: Sets the label to the value associated with the specified key.

methods.name: extractLabel
methods.description: Gets the label value associated with the specified key.

methods.name: toSource
methods.description: Generates a string which, if executed, will return the ObjectStyle.

methods.name: getElements
methods.description: Resolves the object specifier, creating an array of object references.

parameters.name: handler
parameters.description: The event handler. Can accept: File or JavaScript Function.

parameters.name: handler
parameters.description: The registered event handler. Can accept: File or JavaScript Function.
